Addressed to Gaius Asinius Pollio, a supporter of Julius Caesar, who triumphed 39 Rc. over the Parthini, an Illyrian tribe in arms on behalf of Brutus and Cassius. He was a patron of literature, and a friend of Horace and Vergil. The “History of the Civil lVars'' to which Horace here refers comprised the years 60-30 B.c. Pollio was a successful tragic poet as well as an historian, but all his

writings have been lost.
